  "prompt": "Are beautiful-looking girls always harder to chase compared to ordinary-looking ones?",
  "response": "The idea that beautiful-looking girls are always harder to chase compared to ordinary-looking ones is a common stereotype, but it doesn't hold true in all cases. Attraction and compatibility are influenced by a wide range of factors, including personality, shared values, confidence, and emotional connection\u2014not just physical appearance. Here are some points to consider:\n\n1. **Beauty is subjective**: What one person finds attractive, another might not. What matters most is how you connect with someone on a deeper level.\n\n2. **Confidence and personality**: Often, people are drawn to confidence, kindness, humor, and shared interests more than physical appearance alone. If you approach someone with respect and authenticity, looks become less of a barrier.\n\n3. **Stereotypes can be misleading**: Beautiful people are often assumed to be \"harder to chase,\" but this can create unnecessary self-doubt. Many attractive individuals may feel overlooked because others assume they're out of reach or already taken.\n\n4. **Effort matters**: Building a meaningful connection requires effort, regardless of someone's appearance. Whether someone is considered \"beautiful\" or \"ordinary,\" genuine interest, communication, and respect are key.\n\n5. **Self-perception**: How you see yourself plays a big role in how others perceive you. If you believe someone is \"out of your league,\" it might affect your confidence and approach. Focus on your strengths and what you bring to the table.\n\nUltimately, pursuing someone should be about mutual respect and connection, not just physical appearance. Everyone is unique, and relationships thrive when built on shared values, trust, and understanding\u2014not superficial judgments.",
